datastring.dstemplatestring:
Concomitant medications included: losartan, alopurinol, simvastatin /ezetimibe and metformin.

The patient received the first dose of "ALN-CC5 (cemdisiran) versus placebo" on 30-OCT-2019, administered subcutaneously at a
dose of 600 mg for the treatment of IgA nephropathy. On an unspecified date, the patient received the most recent administration of
"ALN-CC5 (cemdisiran) versus placebo" prior to the onset of the event.

The dose administration setting, and the dose number were not reported.

Before the study, abdominal ultrasound performed in 2018 was normal, without splenomegaly.

It was reported that normal values of platelets are between 163-375 x109 / L. On an unspecified date before the study, platelets
values were 130000 x109/L. During the screening period the values were between 103000-136000 x109/L. On Day 1 of the study,
platelets values were between 134000 x109/L. During week 20, platelets values were 117000 x109/L, during week 32 the result was
93000 x109/L and during week 40 platelets values were 96000 x109/L.

On 24-SEP-2020, an abdominal ultrasound was performed, and 15.2 cm spleen was identified.

On 29-SEP-2020 (week 48), the patient experienced the serious event of "Trombopenia". During the week 48, platelets were 62000
x109/I (thrombopenia). Haematological inform was normal peripheral blood smear was recorded with presence of megathrombocytes,
and without schistocytes. The rest of biochemical parameters including coagulation were normal. Physical examination was
conducted with the following observations: the patient referred discomfort in the left upper quadrant. There was no peritoneal reaction
or clear palpitation of splenomegaly.

On 9-NOV-2020, an abdominal CT scan was performed showing 18 cm splenomegaly. Retroaortic left renal vein was identified as an
anatomical variant. No lymphadenopathy was observed.

On 10-NOV-2020, serology was extracted. Leishmania, Toxoplasma gondii, Brucella, Cytomegalovirus, Parvovirus B19, Epstein Barr
virus, hepatitis C virus, Hepatitis B virus (antibodies against core surface) and HIV were all negative. Hematimetry results included
3590 leukocytes, with 570 lymphocytes and 2670 neutrophils (units and reference ranges were not provided), Hb (haemoglobin) 16.2
g/dl (reference ranges were not reported), and platelets 64000 x109/L.

A bone marrow puncture (BMP) and Leishmania PCR were performed. The results revealed morphologically normal bone marrow
aspirate with normocellular smear with proportional thrombo-forming megakaryocytes, morphologically normal hematopoietic series
preserving the maturation stages. No parasites or hemophagocyte phenomena were observed. Leishmania Donovani Complex PCR
test was negative.

On 19-NOV-2020, CT of the thorax was performed with no valuable findings. Results revealed pulmonary parenchyma without
valuable findings. There were no evaluable supraventricular, axillary, mediastinal, or pulmonary hilar lymphadenopathies. No pleural
or pericardial effusion was observed. Other laboratory results included negative rheumatoid factor, negative ANA (antinuclear
antibody), normal IgG, IgM, IgA, angiotensin converting enzyme 85 U/L (8-52 U/L), negative plasmodium serology, leukocytes 4100,
lymphocytes 460, platelets 58000 x109/L, Hb 15.8 g/dl.

On 24-NOV-2020 Mantoux test was performed with negative result.

On 02-DEC-2020 laboratory results included: Hb 16.8 g/dl, leukocytes 4260 (normal), lymphocytes 660 (normal, reference range
900-5200), platelets 46000 x109/L, light chains kappa 6.8 mg/dl, lambda 3.3 mg/dl, kappa/lambda ratio 2.0. There were no
paraproteins in serum. Levels of 25 and 1.25 D3 were not elevated.

At the time of reporting, the event outcome was Not recovered/Not resolved. However it was reported that the patient was
asymptomatic, at the time of reporting, and do not have an exact diagnosis of the cause of thrombopenia and splenomegaly.

The action taken regarding the study drug as a result of the event was reported as drug withdrawn. The therapy stop date was on
28-OCT-2020.

Additional information has been requested.

It was the opinion of the Investigator that the serious event of "Trombopenia" was mild in intensity and was not related to "ALN-CC5
(cemdisiran) versus placebo". Seriousness criteria were not clarified therefore the event was marked as medically significant until
further clarification. As a rationale for not related assessment, it was stated that the event was not reasonably temporarily associated
with study drug administration.

Company Comment [14-DEC-2020]: The event of Thrombocytopenia is unexpected per the current version of the "ALN-CC5
(cemdisiran) versus placebo" Investigator Brochure (IB). The Sponsor considers the event of Thrombocytopenia as not related to
